Method Detail

addTraceTargets

public void addTraceTargets(java.lang.String[] sTargetsNames)
                     throws ScriptingException
Add trace export traget(s) to the trace channel. User can add one or more targets here altough currently ctools trace only support one trace target . If a device has a funnel and multiple sources/exports are hooked up via the funnel to the receiver, user could add multiple trace sources to the channel.

Parameters:
sTargetsNames - name of the trace export - CPU/STM etc. The name should be same as returned by DebugSession::getName().
Throws:
ScriptingException

setupTraceChannel

public void setupTraceChannel(java.lang.String sSettingsFile)
                       throws ScriptingException
Allow User to specify ctool trace channel properties XML file to configure the ctool trace channel.

Parameters:
sSettingsFile - is the file that would have been exported by CCS for a given trace session (via Trace Control).
Throws:
ScriptingException

startTraceRecording

public void startTraceRecording()
                         throws ScriptingException
Configurate Trace Channel driver into recording mode. This function is used for advance user to manually turn on trace recording. In general case, after calling setupTraceChannel function, trace channel is already configured into recording mode.

Throws:
ScriptingException

stopTraceRecording

public void stopTraceRecording()
                        throws ScriptingException
Configurate Trace Channel driver to exit from recording mode. The Channel driver will be in ready mode. User can re-enable recording by calling startTraceRecording() function

Throws:
ScriptingException

                                int iDeviceId,
                                java.lang.String sAppList)
                         throws ScriptingException
Get trace data in text format and save to a file specified by sFileName. The text file contains decoded infomration that could be anlysis by user directly.

Parameters:
sFileName - is the output file name to store trace data. It should include absolute path description.
iDeviceId - for STM this needs to be set to the device id.
sAppList - is the optional application list for STM. The format is =,..,=.
